items.name: Warhammer 40k
items.title: Warhammer 40k
items.headline: Warhammer 40,000 Wiki
items.desc:
"It is the 41st Millennium. For more than a hundred centuries the Emperor of Mankind has sat immobile on the Golden Throne of Earth. He is the master of mankind by the will of the gods and master of a million worlds by the might of his inexhaustible armies. He is a rotting carcass writhing invisibly with power from the Dark Age of Technology. He is the Carrion Lord of the vast Imperium of Man for whom a thousand souls are sacrificed every day so that he may never truly die.Yet even in his deathless state, the Emperor continues his eternal vigilance. Mighty battlefleets cross the daemon-infested miasma of the Warp, the only route between distant stars, their way lit by the Astronomican, the psychic manifestation of the Emperor's will. Vast armies give battle in His name on uncounted worlds. Greatest amongst his soldiers are the Adeptus Astartes, the Space Marines, bio-engineered super-warriors. Their comrades in arms are legion: the Imperial Guard and countless planetary defence forces, the ever-vigilant Inquisition and the tech-priests of the Adeptus Mechanicus to name only a few. But for all their multitudes, they are barely enough to hold off the ever-present threat to humanity from aliens, heretics, mutants -- and far, far worse. To be a man in such times is to be one amongst untold billions. It is to live in the cruelest and most bloody regime imaginable. These are the tales of those times. Forget the power of technology and science, for so much has been forgotten, never to be relearned. Forget the promise of progress and understanding, for in the grim dark future there is only war. There is no peace amongst the stars, only an eternity of carnage and slaughter, and the laughter of thirsting gods." 

Warhammer 40k Wiki is a collaborative project to create the most definitive and accurate reference for everything related to the Warhammer 40,000 universe.

items.name: American Dragon Jake Long
items.title: American Dragon Jake Long
items.headline: Welcome to the American Dragon: Jake Long Wiki!
items.desc:
American Dragon: Jake Long is an American superhero animated television series It marked the first animated Disney Channel Original Series. It produced by Walt Disney Television Animation created by Jeff Goode. It premiered on Disney Channel on January 21, 2005 and was discontinued on September 1, 2007.

Set in New York City (specifically the borough of Manhattan), this animated series tells the story of thirteen-year-old Jake Long who must balance ordinary adolescent transformation with the amazing power and ability to change into the form of a dragon. When he eventually unlocks his full potential and turns into the American Dragon, he will overcome obstacles to protect the magical creatures living in the city, but as his ordinary self, Jake Long can't conquer his huge romantic crush on the pretty blond schoolmate Rose who, unbeknownst to Jake, has a dark, magical secret of her own. She's a natural dragon slayer named Huntsgirl, a member of the Huntsclan that slay dragons. Jake navigates the city with fellow skateboarders Trixie Carter and Arthur P. Spuddinski (A.K.A Spud), and when he gets home, it's to an extended family: a businessman dad originally from the Midwest who doesn't know he's married into a family of dragons from his Chinese wife named Susan. Jake's maternal grandfather Laoshi (who recently immigrated to train his grandson in the magical, mystical ways of the ancient dragons), younger seven-year-old sister Haley (a nascent dragon), and Grandpa's gruff sidekick, a magical Shar-Pei named Fu Dog.

items.name: American Girl Wiki
items.title: American Girl Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the American Girls Dolls Wiki!
items.desc: American Girl is a doll and toy company (originally Pleasant Company, now owned by Mattel) that launched in 1986.   The company's first line, the Historical Characters (rebranded in 2014 to BeForever), focuses on the lives of fictional ten-year old girls that, through books and collections, provide a girl's perspective on noted American historical periods such as the early 20th Century, Civil Rights Era, Native Americans early in history, and the Revolutionary War.   In 1995, a modern era doll line was launched (currently named Truly Me) to focus on modern fashion, clothing, and creativity, along with a baby-doll line. In 2001 a limited edition Girl of the Year was launched to offer modern, named characters with more modern situations and stories and later expanded into Contemporary Characters; in 2016, WellieWishers, a elementary-age targeted line was released.   The American Girl Wiki was founded in July 2008 to offer more presepctive on the brand and its characters, offer continious and steady updates on product releases, and in depth information about the books, stories, and changes. We choose as a Wiki to offer a semi-professional knowledge on all the aspects of the company--not just what has been available to buy, but the various characters and stories that make up the backbone of the company and drive the characters. The wiki is an open resource to not only use, but contribute to and prides itself on being an up-to-date fan-driven resource.

items.name: Merlin Wiki
items.title: Merlin Wiki
items.headline: The magic of Merlin Wiki awaits you...
items.desc:
Merlin Wiki is the number 1, THE BEST place to go to for information on the BBC's magical TV Series starring the young Merlin, King Arthur, the knights of the Round Table, Guinevere, Gaius, Morgana and more. Not only is it THE best place to refer to for information on the show, with videos, almost any picture from the show you can think of, and many wonderful and devoted contributors, it's the best place to go to to meet new people also interested in Merlin. As one user said:
"We all respect one another and we value each other's opinion no matter how different it is to our own. I myself haven't been a member of this wiki for a very long time like some of you, but I can tell that there is a strong vibe of community that almost goes beyond just being members of a fandom. And that it absolutely awesome.

With the new series air date just a month away, I want to thank everyone for being consistantly on the wiki. We all threw in incredible discussions about series 4, and got new insight. I know a lot of us were disappointed with it, namely a few episodes and one particularly annoying uncle. But that's great because where else would we would voice our opinion? Where else would we go to discuss what we liked and what we didn't like on this awesome show. In a way the fact that we all come to this wiki and add pages and thousnads of pictures and even thefact that we complain about the show is one of the reasons it remains so popular! Without a wiki, people would stop watching Merlin because it wouldn't make sense anymore. But everyone here works together to ensure that every fan has a place to go if they're looking for information. Almost every fanfic writer will enventually come here for reference. It's even possible the screenwriters for the show come here to check their facts!"

So please, we welcome you to join Merlin Wiki.Signing up is easy and you will be greeted with the necessary guidance you need to become a great editor!You will be respected and loved. Join us now!

items.title: Mermaid melody Wiki
items.headline: Welcome To The Mermaid Melody Wiki!
items.desc:
This wiki is all about the anime and manga series Mermaid Melody.

Mermaid Melody is an anime and manga aimed at girls aged from 10 to 18. It was created by Michiko Yokote and the artwork was done by Pink Haramoni.
The plot of the story is about Lucia, the Mermaid Princess of the North Pacific Ocean, leaving her castle in the sea to find the boy she saved 7 years ago from a sinking ship. To save the boy, Lucia had entrusted her pink pearl to him. He finds the boy and sees that he is a professional surfer named Kaito Domoto, but Kaito doesn't recognise her because she's disguised in her human form as Lucia Nanami. She can't tell him because if a mermaid reveals her true identity, she will turn into bubbles. Along the series, she tries her best to convince him that she is his mermaid princess.

Meanwhile, Lucia is informed that water demons took over the sea and that she has to gather the other six mermaid princesses from each ocean with their pearls to summon Aqua Regina, the legendary goddess of the sea, so she can stop the water demons. To do this, she teams up with Hanon and Rina, who have both fled to land, and using their pearls, fights the water demons as singing idols.

items.desc: My Bride is a Mermaid Wiki is a free online resource for information about the Seto no Hanayome anime and manga series, distributed in english as "My Bride is a Mermaid".  The manga series was written by Tahiko Kimura and serialized between the September 2002 and May 2009 issues of Monthly Gangan Wing, and the June and December 2010 issues of Monthly Gangan Joker, both published by Square Enix. A 26-episode anime television series adaptation animated by Gonzo and directed by Seiji Kishi aired in Japan on TV Tokyo between April and September 2007. Two original video animation episodes were released in November 2008 and January 2009.
